"title": "5901: loneliness",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5901: loneliness",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>God intends human beings to live together in harmony and to value one another, but Scripture recognises many reasons for individuals to feel unwanted and isolated.</p>\n<h2>Loneliness is not part of God's plan for human beings</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:18\">GEN 2:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps68:5-Ps68:6\">PSA 68:5–68:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa49:15\">ISA 49:15</a></p>\n<h2>God is with his people at all times and in all circumstances</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa41:10\">ISA 41:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut31:8\">DEU 31:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh1:9\">JOS 1:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps27:10\">PSA 27:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa43:2\">ISA 43:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:20\">MAT 28:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:18\">JHN 14:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:5-Heb13:6\">HEB 13:5–13:6</a></p>\n<h2>Reasons why people may experience loneliness</h2>\n<h3>Sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa59:2\">ISA 59:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen4:10-Gen4:12\">GEN 4:10–4:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam28:5-1Sam28:6\">1SA 28:5–28:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps81:11-Ps81:12\">PSA 81:11–81:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa64:7\">ISA 64:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos5:6\">HOS 5:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:18\">EPH 4:18</a></p>\n<h3>Remorse</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:4-Matt27:5\">MAT 27:4–27:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr21:17\">1CH 21:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:75\">MAT 26:75</a></p>\n<h3>Lack of friends</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps142:4\">PSA 142:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:7\">JHN 5:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:18\">JHN 14:18</a></p>\n<h3>Social ostracism</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:9\">JHN 4:9</a></strong> <em>A moral outcast (see <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:18\">Jn 4:18</a>), she was collecting water at the hottest part of the day, when she could do so alone.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:7\">LUK 19:7</a> <em>A Jew who worked for the Roman occupying power was considered a traitor.</em></p>\n<h3>Public shame</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:3\">JHN 8:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:29-Mark15:32\">MRK 15:29–15:32</a></p>\n<h3>Desertion</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim4:16\">2TI 4:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps38:11\">PSA 38:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps88:18\">PSA 88:18</a></p>\n<h3>Loss of family</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:12\">LUK 7:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth1:3-Ruth1:5\">RUT 1:3–1:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam18:33\">2SA 18:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs4:1\">2KI 4:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job1:20-Job1:21\">JOB 1:20–1:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps27:10\">PSA 27:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt2:17-Matt2:18\">MAT 2:17–2:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:15\">JER 31:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:5\">1TI 5:5</a></p>\n<h3>Loss of identity</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:27\">LUK 8:27</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:2-Mark5:3\">MRK 5:2–5:3</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:30\">LUK 8:30</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:9\">MRK 5:9</a></p>\n<h3>Discontent</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl4:8\">ECC 4:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl2:10-Eccl2:11\">ECC 2:10–2:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl2:18\">ECC 2:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:5-Heb13:6\">HEB 13:5–13:6</a></p>\n<h3>Disability</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:2\">ACT 3:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev21:17-Lev21:18\">LEV 21:17–21:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:32\">MAT 9:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:22\">MAT 12:22</a></p>\n<h3>Disease</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke17:12\">LUK 17:12</a></strong> <em>Lepers were forbidden to mix with those not affected.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev13:4\">LEV 13:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num5:1-Num5:3\">NUM 5:1–5:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs7:3\">2KI 7:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr26:21\">2CH 26:21</a></p>\n<h3>Insomnia</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps102:7\">PSA 102:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job7:4\">JOB 7:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan6:18\">DAN 6:18</a></p>\n<h3>Depression</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs19:4\">1KI 19:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut33:27\">DEU 33:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job7:16\">JOB 7:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps43:5\">PSA 43:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps73:16-Ps73:17\">PSA 73:16–73:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer15:10\">JER 15:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic7:1\">MIC 7:1</a></p>\n<h3>Poverty</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov19:7\">PRO 19:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs17:12\">1KI 17:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov19:4\">PRO 19:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:14-Luke15:16\">LUK 15:14–15:16</a></p>\n<h3>Old age</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps71:9\">PSA 71:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam19:34-2Sam19:35\">2SA 19:34–19:35</a></p>\n<h3>Dying and the approach of death</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps23:4\">PSA 23:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps18:4-Ps18:6\">PSA 18:4–18:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:38-Rom8:39\">ROM 8:38–8:39</a></p>\n<h2>Loneliness experienced as a consequence of God's calling</h2>\n<h3>God's setting apart for service</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs19:10\">1KI 19:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg6:14-Judg6:15\">JDG 6:14–6:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer1:5\">JER 1:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer4:18-Jer4:19\">JER 4:18–4:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer15:16-Jer15:17\">JER 15:16–15:17</a></p>\n<h3>Leadership</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:32\">MRK 10:32</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod24:1-Exod24:2\">EXO 24:1–24:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh1:6-Josh1:7\">JOS 1:6–1:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:17-Matt20:19\">MAT 20:17–20:19</a></p>\n<h3>Responsibility</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num11:14\">NUM 11:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod18:17-Exod18:18\">EXO 18:17–18:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor11:28\">2CO 11:28</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ experienced loneliness</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:46\">MAT 27:46</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:33-Mark15:34\">MRK 15:33–15:34</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps22:1-Ps22:2\">PSA 22:1–22:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:1-Matt4:2\">MAT 4:1–4:2</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:1-Luke4:2\">LUK 4:1–4:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt14:23\">MAT 14:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:28-Luke4:30\">LUK 4:28–4:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:67\">JHN 6:67</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John16:32\">JHN 16:32</a></p>\n<h2>Positive aspects of loneliness</h2>\n<h3>Solitude provides an opportunity for communion with God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:6\">MAT 6:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod3:1-Exod3:2\">EXO 3:1–3:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod33:9\">EXO 33:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs4:32-2Kgs4:33\">2KI 4:32–4:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:39\">MAT 26:39</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:35\">MRK 1:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:45-Mark6:46\">MRK 6:45–6:46</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:9\">REV 1:9</a></p>\n<h3>Engaging in spiritual warfare</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen32:24\">GEN 32:24</a></strong></p>\n<h3>The opportunity for spiritual experiences away from the crowd</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:2\">MRK 9:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan10:8\">DAN 10:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor12:2-2Cor12:4\">2CO 12:2–12:4</a></p>\n<h3>Solitude as rest from the turmoil of everyday life</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:31-Mark6:32\">MRK 6:31–6:32</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:28\">MAT 11:28</a></p>",
